    "messageBody": "<div id=\"ygrps-yiv-288520868\"><html>\n\n<head>\n \n\n\n \n \n \n \n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n<style>\n<!--\n#ygrps-yiv-288520868  \n _filtered #ygrps-yiv-288520868 {font-family:Tahoma;panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;}\n#ygrps-yiv-288520868  \n#ygrps-yiv-288520868 p.ygrps-yiv-288520868MsoNormal, #ygrps-yiv-288520868 li.ygrps-yiv-288520868MsoNormal, #ygrps-yiv-288520868 div.ygrps-yiv-288520868MsoNormal\n\t{margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:12.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\n#ygrps-yiv-288520868 a:link, #ygrps-yiv-288520868 span.ygrps-yiv-288520868MsoHyperlink\n\t{color:blue;text-decoration:underline;}\n#ygrps-yiv-288520868 a:visited, #ygrps-yiv-288520868 span.ygrps-yiv-288520868MsoHyperlinkFollowed\n\t{color:blue;text-decoration:underline;}\n#ygrps-yiv-288520868 tt\n\t{font-family:\"Courier New\";}\n#ygrps-yiv-288520868 span.ygrps-yiv-288520868EmailStyle18\n\t{font-family:Arial;color:navy;}\n _filtered #ygrps-yiv-288520868 {margin:1.0in 1.25in 1.0in 1.25in;}\n#ygrps-yiv-288520868 div.ygrps-yiv-288520868Section1\n\t{}\n-->\n</style>\n\n</head>\n\n \n\n<div class=\"ygrps-yiv-288520868Section1\">\n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-288520868MsoNormal\"><font size=\"2\" color=\"navy\" face=\"Arial\"><span style='\nfont-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:navy;'>An in between is to have the unit tests in\nthe same package, but in different directories. <span\n style=''>&nbsp;</span>This at leasts allows for you to test public\nand package as well as have them separated&#8230;.just a thought.</span></font></p> \n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-288520868MsoNormal\"><font size=\"2\" color=\"navy\" face=\"Arial\"><span style='\nfont-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:navy;'> &nbsp;</span></font></p> \n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-288520868MsoNormal\"><font size=\"2\" color=\"navy\" face=\"Arial\"><span style='\nfont-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:navy;'> &nbsp;</span></font></p> \n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-288520868MsoNormal\"><font size=\"2\" color=\"navy\" face=\"Arial\"><span style='\nfont-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:navy;'> &nbsp;</span></font></p> \n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-288520868MsoNormal\" style='margin-left:.5in;'><font size=\"2\" face=\"Tahoma\"><span\n style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Tahoma;'>-----Original Message-----<br>\n<b><span style='font-weight:bold;'>From:</span></b> Stevens, Timothy J.\n(LNG-MBC) [mailto:timothy.j.stevens@...] <br>\n<b><span style='font-weight:bold;'>Sent:</span></b> </span></font>\n<font size=\"2\" face=\"Tahoma\"><span style='\nfont-size:10.0pt;font-family:Tahoma;'>Friday, March 29, 2002</span></font><font\n size=\"2\" face=\"Tahoma\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Tahoma;'> </span></font>\n<font size=\"2\" face=\"Tahoma\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Tahoma;'>12:47 PM</span></font><font size=\"2\" face=\"Tahoma\"><span\n style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Tahoma;'><br>\n<b><span style='font-weight:bold;'>To:</span></b> &#39;junit@yahoogroups.com&#39;<br>\n<b><span style='font-weight:bold;'>Subject:</span></b> RE: [junit] testing\nprivate methods</span></font></p>\n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-288520868MsoNormal\" style='margin-left:.5in;'><font size=\"3\" face=\"Times New Roman\"><span\n style='font-size:12.0pt;'> &nbsp;</span></font></p> \n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-288520868MsoNormal\" style='margin-left:.5in;'><font size=\"2\" face=\"Courier New\"><span\n style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\"Courier New\";'><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Many of my tests\nwind up being nearly as long as the class being</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">tested... I have no desire to double the size of\nmy code with tests. Plus,</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">tests that exist within the classes they are\ntesting will ultimately get</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">compiled along with the classes, increasing the\nsize of your distributions</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">needlessly.</font></tt><br>\n<br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I go with the\nseparate-yet-parallel directory structure route, and</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">tend to make most methods protected rather than\nprivate to allow them to be</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">tested. I&#39;m sure someone will chime in shortly for\nlogic surrounding only</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">testing public methods.</font></tt><br>\n<br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -tim</font></tt><br>\n<br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">-----Original Message-----</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">From: David Stagner [mailto:dstagner@...]</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">Sent: </font></tt></span></font>\n<tt><font size=\"2\" face=\"Courier New\"><span\n style='font-size:10.0pt;'>Friday, March 29, 2002</span></font></tt><tt><font\n size=\"2\" face=\"Courier New\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'> </span></font></tt>\n<tt><font size=\"2\" face=\"Courier New\"><span\n style='font-size:10.0pt;'>2:38 PM</span></font></tt><font size=\"2\"\n face=\"Courier New\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\"Courier New\";'><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">To: junit@yahoogroups.com</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">Subject: Re: [junit] testing private methods</font></tt><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">Nilesh Thali wrote:</font></tt><br>\n<br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; Actually, we would like to keep our tests as\na completely separate package</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">to</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; prevent it from obscuring the actual code\nbase...</font></tt><br>\n<br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">Choose your poison, then. If you want to keep your\ntest classes </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">completely separate from the classes tested, then\nyou&#39;ll only be testing </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">the public interface (and you need to feel certain\nall your private </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">methods work when they can only be tested\nindirectly via the public </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">interface). If you want to test private methods\ndirectly, you must run </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">your tests as inner classes.</font></tt><br>\n<br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">Why do you think tests &quot;obscure&quot; the\ncode base, though? If you use an </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">inner class, just put it at the very bottom of the\nsource file, and </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">programmers should be able to just ignore it. If\nyou use a consistent </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">naming scheme, programmers can also ignore test\nmethods in whatever IDE </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">you&#39;re using. Alternately, you could put the tests\nin separate classes </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">in the same package, so you can test package-local\nmethods.</font></tt><br>\n<br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">Personally, i don&#39;t like the idea of putting unit\ntests in a separate </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">package, for two reasons - first, the tests would\nonly have access to </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">public methods, not package or private methods.\nThis makes test-first </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">coding harder, as the private methods can only be\nobserved indirectly. </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">And second, it makes it too easy to ignore the\ntest suite, &quot;just this </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">one time&quot;, which leads to untested code. But\nthis is very much my own </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">opinion on how things should be done.</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">-- </font></tt><br>\n<br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">David Stagner</font></tt><br>\n<br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">National Marrow Donor Program</font></tt><br>\n</span></font><tt><font size=\"2\" face=\"Courier New\"><span\n style='font-size:10.0pt;'>3001 Broadway Street NE</span></font></tt><font\n size=\"2\" face=\"Courier New\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\"Courier New\";'><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">Broadway Ridge </font></tt></span></font><tt><font\n size=\"2\" face=\"Courier New\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>Suite</span></font></tt><tt><font\n size=\"2\" face=\"Courier New\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'> 500</span></font></tt><font\n size=\"2\" face=\"Courier New\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\"Courier New\";'><br>\n</span></font><tt><font size=\"2\" face=\"Courier New\"><span\n style='font-size:10.0pt;'>Minneapolis</span></font></tt><tt><font\n size=\"2\" face=\"Courier New\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>, </span></font></tt><tt><font\n size=\"2\" face=\"Courier New\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>MN</span></font></tt><tt><font\n size=\"2\" face=\"Courier New\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&nbsp; </span></font></tt><tt><font\n size=\"2\" face=\"Courier New\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>55413</span></font></tt><font\n size=\"2\" face=\"Courier New\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\"Courier New\";'><br>\n<br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">Email: dstagner@...</font></tt><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">To unsubscribe from this group, send an email to:</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">junit-unsubscribe@yahoogroups.com</font></tt><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">Your use of Yahoo! Groups is subject to <a rel=\"nofollow\"\n target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://docs.yahoo.com/info/terms/\">http://docs.yahoo.com/info/terms/</a> </font></tt><br>\n<br>\n</span></font><br style=''>\n<br style=''>\n</p> \n\n<tt><font size=\"2\"\n face=\"Courier New\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>To unsubscribe from this\ngroup, send an email to:</span></font></tt><font size=\"2\" face=\"Courier New\"><span\n style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\"Courier New\";'><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">junit-unsubscribe@yahoogroups.com</font></tt><br>\n</span></font><br>\n<br>\n<tt><font size=\"2\" face=\"Courier New\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>Your use of\nYahoo! Groups is subject to the <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://docs.yahoo.com/info/terms/\">Yahoo!\nTerms of Service</a>.</span></font></tt> \n\n</div>\n\n \n\n</html></div>", 
